-- Taiwan Stocks: Advantech, Pegatron, VIA Technologies, Wintek
-- B y   A d e l a   L i n
-- 2012-01-03T06:02:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/taiwan-stocks-advantech-pegatron-via-technologies-wintek.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in  Taiwan trading. (TWSE)  Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 1.5 percent to 7,053.38, the biggest
gain since Dec. 23.  Advantech Co. (2395)  (2395 TT) climbed 2.6 percent to NT$84.20,
the highest close since Dec. 7. Advantech bought 18 million
shares of Advansus Corp. for NT$306 million ($10.1 million) from
 Pegatron Corp. (4938)  (4938 TT). Pegatron advanced 2.8 percent to
NT$33.30, the highest since Nov. 4.  VIA Technologies Inc. (2388)  (2388 TT) fell 1.9 percent to
NT$15.35, the lowest close since Dec. 19. The maker of
integrated chipsets said its unconsolidated sales in December
dropped 31 percent from a year earlier to NT$267.3 million,
according to a statement to the Taiwan stock exchange.  Wintek Corp. (2384)  (2384 TT) added 1.6 percent to NT$22, the
highest close since Dec. 5. The maker of liquid-crystal displays
said December consolidated sales rose 34 percent from a year
earlier to NT$10.6 billion. Consolidated sales for 2011
increased 45 percent to NT$93.8 billion, it said in a stock-
exchange filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adela Lin in Taipei at 
 alin95@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
